CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 13, 1953, pg. 11, reads: "NEW LINKS - These five charming young matron were initiated into the Pittsburgh chapter of the Links, Inc., Monday night at a gala affair held at member Daisy Lampkin's home. The solemn ritual brought into the national group Mrs. Mai Ratcliffe, Mabel Bookert, Mary Jane Page, Elizabeth Younge and Miriam Fountain.  Following the installation, the Links were joined by their husbands for a gay social hour. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of five women, Mai Ratcliffe, Mabel Bookert, Mary Jane Page, Elizabeth Younge, and Miriam Fountain, posed behind table for initiation into Links Club, in home of Daisy Lampkin with floral wallpaper
